  <caaml:metaData>
    <caaml:comment>Observed: CD, SW&#13;
Plotted: CD&#13;
Objective: Investigate the depth of moisture penetration and the general structure of the spring snowpack at TL.&#13;
Site: A steep, natural roll running parallel to a seldom-traveled snow road in rolling terrain at TL. Area punctuated by sparse stands of mature conifer. Predominantly shaded feature which may see late spring sun. Likely saw some loading throughout the season.&#13;
Notes: March 5th MFcr identified down 125 cm. &lt; 5mm and very brittle.</caaml:comment>
